---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
import Avatar from '../components/Avatar.astro';
---

<Layout title="Luke Batchelor - Developer">
  <div class="space-y-8 max-w-xl">
    <Avatar />

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p class="text-3xl font-semibold">G'day!</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        I'm Luke - a Perth-based Senior Fullstack Engineer with a decade of experience building
        things at every scale.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <p class="font-semibold text-xl">Work</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        Most of my career has been at Atlassian, where I helped found and scale the Frontend
        Monorepo from a single design system into a behemoth of a monorepo powering dozens of apps (including Jira and Confluence) and thousands of frontend packages. A few things
        I'm proud of:
      </p>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Changesets</span> - original author of the early
          versions, now open-sourced and used across hundreds of open source projects
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Landkid</span> - original co-author of Atlassian's
          frontend merge queue, a vital tool in preventing semantic conflicts in a repo that merges 200+ PRs a day
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">DX & CI/CD at scale</span> - built and maintained hundreds of pipelines for the building, testing, type-checking and deployment of thousands of frontend packages.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p class="font-semibold text-xl">Home</p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        I'm one of the lucky people who gets to do their passion as a job and then comes home and
        keeps doing it.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        On weekends I'm almost always building something; from small games, micro-apps, PWA's, tools, etc to full stack applications and automations for my home, events, fundraisers, comedy shows, small business backends, etc  
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">A couple I'm most proud of:
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text-muted list-disc pl-5">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Generozity</span> - A platform my brother and I built for the Generozity group to raise money for charity (so far, more than $800,000!). It includes a donation portal, an admin interface and a live OBS overlay for use during livestreams.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-text">Rap GPT</span> - A platform for building and running crowd + LLM powered Freestyle Rap games for the amazing Macshane. It's been presented at dozens of packed out shows from Perth WA, to Edinborough Fringe!
        </li>
      </ul>
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted">
        Other times though, I just love coding for the sake of it, working with creative constraints just to see if something is possible. This has lead to some odd projects like: pure CSS apps (a binary decoder, a rhythm game, a tic tac toe AI and even a "mind reading app" 😂), a code golfed game of Snake
        encoded entirely in a URL and even a palindromic, symmetric tattoo in a profanely named esoteric programming
        language.
      </p>
    </div>

    <a href="/projects" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm inline-block">
      View my projects →
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
